Children should wear a well-fitted mask that overs the nose, mouth and chin. There are three types of masks that WHO recommends for the public*: reusable non-medical masks that comply with standardsdisposable medical masks other types of reusable non-medical masks, including homemade multi-layered (fabric) masks are acceptable when other options are not available.*More on the types of masks, how to choose them, and how to wear them is available here:  https://www.who.int/emergencies/diseases/novel-coronavirus-2019/advice-for-public/when-and-how-to-use-masks 
